│ Cause Analysis: In `tryToReuseLCSSAPhi`, after converting a pointer phi to  │
│ integer via `getPtrToIntExpr`, we must check if the result is               │
│ `CouldNotCompute`. If it is, we should skip this phi and continue to the    │
│ next one. Currently, the code proceeds to compute `Diff =                   │
│ SE.getMinusSCEV(S, ExitSCEV)` without checking, leading to the crash.\n\n4. │
